			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I agree with you Mayhem, not necessarily with how you said it, but I still agree. Sevent, I for one can say that I have never begged for anything in my life of playing eq. I started back with my druid in RiverVale. Going out, killing, selling, and repeating over and over. Then when I made lvl 10 with him, I found the guts to venture outside my homecity to Kelthin where I started hunting in Crush Bone. I guess sometimes people forget how easy it is to merchant. I started by saving myself 15pp and buying my first dragoon dirk, selling it again for 20pp. I worked my way up so that now as a lvl 24 gnome warrior I have full crafted armor, 2yks, and good jewelry. I earned every item and every cent I own, not one CP of which was obtained through begging.  It is very possible to obtain good equipment with out begging, lots of people are just too damn lazy to get out and actyually WORK for what they want. Just my opinion.<p>

							

